Scan **grouping** now uses a hand-rolled BK-tree (Hamming metric) for near-duplicate candidate search instead of the O(N²) all-pairs pHash scan — on a ~16k-candidate library that cuts the dominant ~128M pairwise comparisons to roughly O(N log N), so the grouping stage no longer runs for minutes. The grouping verdict is unchanged: every gate (mean-color #462, dHash #524, source priority) still runs per surviving pair, so output is bit-identical to the previous brute-force pass (proven by `TestBKTreeParity`). ([#526](https://github.com/jackal998/photo-manager/issues/526))
